<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-26T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-26T20:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/567</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-26T20:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>915. Your 1088, February 23, 5 p.m. All Spanish vessels in American
                                ports desiring to sail may leave freely and bunker licenses will be
                                granted and without the imposition of any conditions. The foregoing
                                does not include permission to take cargo for which export licenses
                                have not been granted or have been revoked. This is in accordance
                                with our previous cables which we regret were not fully
                                understood.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>